<br>
There is no question that playing a bard is fun, perhaps the most fun class to play in EQ.  That's why I played one for as long as I did. (Born August 15, 1999, level 57 when Velious came out, retired at level 5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  <br>
<br>
But there is more to EQ than enjoying the class that you play.  At later levels (57+) when Sebilis, HS, and other high level zones start turning green, the regular 6 person group begins to lose relevance.  Big time raids become the object of the game, and they are Verant's intended major source of satisfaction of game-play.  (The next addition to EQ is supposed provide an alternative to big time raids for the 57+ crowd). For big time raids, bards are an after thought.  Yes, one or two bards would be nice for a raid, and a good raid should have one for occlusion and the bard's epic proc.  But nobody is going to call off a raid if no bards are available. That's why there are rarely more than one or two bards in the major raiding guilds on this server.  Given their importance in the endgame, there is, frankly, a miniscule demand for them.  <br>
<br>
Sure, bards are valued for old world fear, hate, and dragon raids.  But the lower 50 raiding are a completely different word from the upper 50 raiding.  For the endgame you want the best, not the jack of all trades.  You want warriors, clerics, and rogues.  Then you want the best support classes, which are shamans and enchanters.  Then you want secondary tanks and nukers.  You want the best jack of all trades?  You don't look for a bard, you look for a druid.  Solid healing, solid nukes, good buffs, all very important.  After you have all that, then you look for your bard.        <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chants</A> at: 8/17/01 9:38:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udandelioness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dandelioness</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/17/01 9:18:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards are the best class.</span><hr size=1> that is very true, bards dont need to tank, they can do enough for the group just by singing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
